properties.headline: Flood Watch issued January 21 at 9:34PM PST until January 24 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
The Flood Watch continues for

* Portions of northwest Washington and west central Washington,
including the following counties, in northwest Washington,
Skagit and Whatcom. In west central Washington, King, Lewis,
Pierce, Snohomish, and Thurston.

* From Thursday afternoon through Friday afternoon

* A period of warming, rising snow levels, and heavy rain in the
mountains will force sharp rises on the rivers flowing off the
Cascades. Snow levels will rise to around 5,000 to 7,000 feet
with 3 to 6 inches of rain in the mountains late Wednesday
through Saturday. Locally heavier amounts are possible. Minor
flooding is possible on several rivers as a result.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Watch means there is a potential for flooding based on
current forecasts.

You should monitor latest forecasts and be alert for possible
Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be
prepared to take action should flooding develop.

NWSheadline: FLOOD WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH FRIDAY AFTERNOON
